--downgrade Downgrades the version [args= version to downgrade to] 
--preview-name [args=none] shows the name
--virtual [args= name of virtual env]
--activate [args none] activates virtual env. (can be paired directly with virtual.)
--scan-dir [args= dir to scan] (use --scan or --type to specify what to scan for)
--type [args= type to scan for] can be paired with scan flags.
--contains [args= String (parameter that specifies what we should look for)] can be paired with type and scan flags
--install
--install-needed pairs with virtual and activate.
--new allows you to create new something
--location allows you to specify where (can be paired with new)
--scan-project
>> allows you to redirect to file
--and allows you to specify an "and" condition (Paired with >>)
--target
--set-root
--append used with scan to append results instead of override
--export
--export-config
--start (start something)
--remove-type Remove all of a type
--delete (delete a file)
--delete-type (delete all of a type) (Can be paired with contains so its conditional.)
--create starts the auto create project/build... It will auto ask you everything needed for a build.
--show-console true/false -> for a build wether or not we should have the console shown.
--auto (tries to automatically do everything on its own. Including find a splash screen, inject splash, etc...) If you specify something like --auto --inject splash the program will try and find an optimal spot to inject the code to turn off splash screen once program launches.
--backup 